Meet <b>Mya</b>, our citizen of the week! <br><br>Mya lives at 46790 Main Street in Metro Park. She knew when she moved to Millsberry on March 18, 2005, that she wanted to be just a hop, skip, and a jump away from all the downtown action. With shopping, school, and sports facilities at her fingertips, she has her finger on the pulse of what's hip and new in town.<br><br>What sets Mya apart from other citizens is her diverse tastes. It's not unusual to find her studying in her bedroom while listening to jazz and classical music, nor is it out of character for her to spend hours in the <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=12">Home Entertainment Superstore </a> checking out all the latest gizmos and gadgets. A technological whiz and a music lover (though drum 'n' bass is more her style when she's not hitting the books), Mya is definitely hard to categorize.<br><br>When asked what she has planned for the holiday season, she replied, "I'll probably continue to renovate my house, and I'm always looking for violet clothes and accessories because violet is one of my favorite colors. Also, I think I'll take more lessons at the <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/communitycenter/dojo/">dojo</a> because I've had an interest in martial arts since before I moved to Millsberry and haven't had time to keep up my training. With some time off from school I should be able to fit some more exercise in." <br><br>She'll undoubtedly be a fixture at Peabody Park's ice hockey rink, where her searing slap shot has gained her notoriety among the goalies. Talk about a girl who never fails to surprise! We're sure she'll continue to make friends and expand her reputation as a wild card. So get to know this quirky citizen now and you'll be sure to cross paths with her where you least expect it.<br><br>Thanks for being a good citizen, Mya, and congratulations on being named Millsberry's citizen of the week!<br></div>
